Common.LongDescription.Common.Text: The suite is located in 250 South Oak Way, positioned in the heart of Green Park office park. Internally the office has fully raised floors with a suspended ceiling and Cat II lighting. The office is currently fitted with open plan work stations (16 desks), 4 glazed offices, a board room and a kitchenette. 250 South Oak Way is a modern multi occupier building positioned at the heart of Green Park on Lime Square. Lime Square is the central amenity offering for Green Park and offers a range of facilities including Nuffield Health & Fitness club, Zest Bar & Brasserie, WH Smith.

Common.FloorPlans.Common.ImageCaption: NO2 FORBURY PLACE UPPER FLOOR PLAN

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text: Forbury Place’s prime location offers all the lifestyle benefits you’d expect, with high street retail, restaurants and bars, local heritage, and the relaxing green spaces of Forbury Gardens all within a short walk. Transport links are equally impressive with abundant car parking, easy connections to the motorway network, Reading Station a five-minute walk away and plenty of public transport nearby, it’s an impeccably well-connected development. Forbury Place is no ordinary office development. This landmark building combines striking architectural features with the flexible yet efficient use of floorspace that’s the hallmark of today’s most progressive office developments.  The stunning double-height reception provides a preview of the high quality finishes that extend throughout the building’s large floor plates.

No.3 Forbury Place offers high quality non-fitted office space on part of the 10th floor. Featuring an enhanced reception, external landscaping and a new eatery ‘Forbury Kitchen’ serving the wider Forbury Place Estate. Home to Yell, Pegasystems, Convatec, Osborne Clarke, PwC and BPP, the size and scale of this development is what you would expect of a prestigious Central London development. Designed on truly out-of-town scale it cements Reading’s position as a key business hub outside the Capital. The available accommodation has been refurbished in its entirety, along with an enhanced reception, landscaping and a ‘the Forbury kitchen’.
